#: includes/Core/class-cache-health.php:81
msgid "Persistent object cache is active"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Core/class-cache-health.php:84
msgid "The theme caches anonymous product-grid responses (load-more, filtering, sorting) in the persistent object cache, so paginated catalog requests are served without recomputing their query."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Core/class-cache-health.php:95
msgid "No persistent object cache — catalog cache is inactive"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Core/class-cache-health.php:98
msgid "Aggressive Apparel caches anonymous product-grid responses (load-more, filtering, sorting) only when a persistent object cache is available. Without one, every catalog request recomputes its query and re-renders from scratch, which will not hold up under traffic."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Core/class-cache-health.php:101
msgid "How to fix: install and enable a persistent object cache backed by Redis or Memcached. Most managed WordPress hosts offer this as a one-click add-on; self-hosted sites install the Redis/Memcached server plus a drop-in plugin (for example Redis Object Cache), which writes wp-content/object-cache.php. Additionally place a full-page cache (Varnish, Batcache, or a host/CDN page cache) in front of anonymous archive traffic, configured to bypass cart, checkout, and my-account and to vary on the WooCommerce session cookies — only paginated load-more is theme-cached; the initial archive paint relies on the page cache."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Core/class-cache-health.php:108
msgid "Learn about object caching"
msgstr ""

